will provide self report probes during half of the trials and psychophysiological recordings will be taken for the other half of the trials half of these subjects will also undergo functional magnetic resonance imaging fmri scanning while participating in the mid task it is expected that younger adults will show errors in affective forecasting of arousal for anticipation but not of valence for incentive outcomes it is also predicted that anticipation of gains will activate the ventral striatum which will be correlated with psychophysiological indices of arousal and positive valence a comparison of younger and older adults will demonstrate whether affective forecasting improves with age experience which will help to understand how older adults make long term choices and how to optimize those choices this study is a seed project for the center on the demography and economics of health and aging contact nomita divi search chp search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 736 0815 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
